# Create and Delete a Folder via the ApiDeck File Storage API

## Background
Your SaaS backend needs to provision short-lived workspaces in a customer's connected cloud drive (OneDrive in this environment) and tear them down after use. ApiDeck's File Storage Unified API exposes a single normalized REST surface for File Storage providers, so the same code path works for OneDrive, Google Drive, Dropbox, Box, and SharePoint. In this task you will exercise both the `Create Folder` and `Delete Folder` endpoints against the preconfigured OneDrive connector, and prove the round trip via a log file.

## Requirements
- Write a Python program that, when executed, uses the ApiDeck File Storage Unified API to:
  1. Resolve the OneDrive drive whose `name` matches the value of the `APIDECK_FILE_STORAGE_DRIVE_NAME` environment variable.
  2. Create a brand-new folder inside the root of that drive, whose `name` is built from a fixed prefix and the current `run-id` (see Implementation Hints).
  3. Delete that same folder using its returned `id`.
  4. Append a structured log of the operation to `/home/user/myproject/output.log`.
- The script must call the real ApiDeck API; do not stub or mock responses.
- All ApiDeck requests must use the `onedrive` service id since multiple connectors may be active in the workspace.

## Implementation Hints
- Read every credential and identifier from environment variables. The following are guaranteed to be present in the execution environment: `APIDECK_APP_ID`, `APIDECK_API_KEY`, `APIDECK_CONSUMER_ID`, `APIDECK_FILE_STORAGE_DRIVE_NAME`, `ZEALT_RUN_ID`.
- You can use either the official `apideck-unify` Python SDK (preinstalled) or plain `requests` against `https://unify.apideck.com`. The required request headers are documented in the research plan (`Authorization`, `x-apideck-app-id`, `x-apideck-consumer-id`, `x-apideck-service-id`).
- The drive id is **not** the same as the drive name. Use `GET /file-storage/drives` (or the SDK equivalent) to list drives and find the one whose `name` equals the value of `APIDECK_FILE_STORAGE_DRIVE_NAME`, then keep its `id`.
- When creating the folder, the `parent_folder_id` for the drive root is the literal string `"root"`. Include `drive_id` in the create request so the folder is created in the resolved drive.
- Make every externally visible resource collision-free by suffixing the `run-id` (from the `ZEALT_RUN_ID` env var). For this task, the folder `name` must be exactly `harbor-delete-${ZEALT_RUN_ID}`.
- After deletion, write the log file with one `key: value` per line so it can be parsed by a downstream verifier.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Project path: /home/user/myproject
- Ensure the script is executed and the artifacts exist (the folder must really be created and then deleted on OneDrive via ApiDeck).
- Log file: /home/user/myproject/output.log
- The log file must contain these three lines, in any order, each on its own line:
  - `Drive ID: <drive_id>` — the ApiDeck unified id of the resolved drive.
  - `Created folder ID: <folder_id>` — the unified id returned by the Create Folder call.
  - `Deleted folder ID: <folder_id>` — the unified id passed to the Delete Folder call. It must match the created folder id.
